title: Led Zeppelin 1980 Tour Over Europe A Best Of Compilation FLAC
description:
Led Zeppelin 1980 Tour Over Europe A Best Of Compilation FLAC

SOURCES:
All tracks Soundboard sourced, except Tracks 2 and 17, 
which are SBD-AUD matrix sourced. 

TRACK LISTING:
01. Train Kept A-Rollin' - Frankfurt, June 3
02. Nobody's Fault but Mine - Cologne, June 18
03. Black Dog - Zurich, June 29
04. In the Evening - Zurich, June 29
05. The Rain Song - Zurich, June 29
06. Hot Dog - Rotterdam, June 21
07. All My Love - Frankfurt, June 30
08. Trampled Under Foot - Frankfurt, June 30
09. Since I've Been Loving You - Brussels, June 20
10. Achilles Last Stand - Zurich, June 29
11. White Summer / Black Mountain Side - Zurich, June 29 
12. Kashmir - Frankfurt, June 30
13. Stairway to Heaven - Zurich, June 29
14. Rock & Roll - Berlin, July 7 
15. Money (That's What I Want) - Frankfurt, June 30 
16. Heartbreaker - Rotterdam, June 21
17. Communication Breakdown - Mannheim, July 3
18. Whole Lotta Love - Berlin, July 7

PROCESSING: 
All tracks have been processed with light reverb, 
between 10% and 20%. 

Many tracks have been given a modest bass 
boost in the 40-80Hz range. 

Additional processing or repairs 
have been done to selected tracks, as detailed below.


ARTWORK: 
This cover artwork is original. 
For better or worse, you won't find it anywhere else.
The photos on each show's cover are, to the best of 
my knowledge, from that show.

*** SINCERE THANKS: ***
Weedwacker, Winston, bluecongo, and KRW_CO 
for their great source liberations, transfers, mastering, and 
remastering. bluecongo and everyone else on R-O for their wise 
suggestions and input about the best performances of the 1980 tour.
Any credit for this package is shared with them. Any problems with 
this packet are mine alone. 

DISCLAIMER: 
These track selections are mine. 
Some are general consensus picks, while in other cases my 
preferences diverge from others' (Kashmir, for example). 
Despite how dry they are in raw form, I've stuck exclusively to 
soundboard (or matrix) sources. Overall I prefer these sources 
with some processing, to the available audience sources.


INDIVIDUAL SOURCE INFORMATION:
Cologne, June 18: Winston Remasters Live Omega Series 
Brussels June 20: Winston Remasters Live Omega Series 
Rotterdam, June 21: KRW_CO, 1st gen
Zurich, June 29: Weedwacker Soundboard series 
Frankfurt, June 30: Weedweacker, Soundboard Series
Mannheim, July 3: bluecongo, "Mannheim Steamroller"
Berlin, July 7: Weedwacker, Soundboard Series

LED ZEPPELIN:
Jimmy Page: Guitars
Robert Plant: Vocals
John Bonham: Drums
John Paul Jones: Bass, Keyboards
